{
  "analysis": "We inspected input.csv and expected.csv. Each line in input has three comma-separated fields with irregular spaces and mixed case, e.g., '  alpha1  ,    BeTa1   ,  GaMmA1'. The expected lines have: fields reversed order (3rd;2nd;1st), semicolon separators, all uppercase, and ';OK' appended, e.g., 'GAMMA1;BETA1;ALPHA1;OK'. Both files have 1,000,000 lines; expected is smaller due to removed spaces and shorter delimiters. We need to implement the transformation using three distinct Vim macros (registers a, b, c), within allowed script commands only. We'll create macros to: (a) remove all whitespace per line, (b) reorder the three fields and convert delimiter to semicolons, (c) uppercase the line and append ';OK'. We'll write /app/apply_macros.vim with only call setreg lines, :%normal! executions, and :wq, then run Vim headlessly and verify the result matches expected.csv.",
  "plan": "- Create /app/apply_macros.vim using a here-doc containing only allowed commands. Macros:\n  - a: :s/\\s\\+//g to strip all whitespace on the current line.\n  - b: :s/^(first),(second),(third)$/third;second;first/ using capture groups to reorder and change delimiters.\n  - c: gUU to uppercase the current line, then A;OK<Esc> to append ';OK'.\n- Execute the script headlessly on /app/input.csv with Vim.\n- Verify the output matches /app/expected.csv byte-for-byte using cmp or diff.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "cat > /app/apply_macros.vim <<'EOF'\ncall setreg('a', \":s/\\s\\+//g\\<CR>\")\ncall setreg('b', \":s/^\\([^,]*\\),\\([^,]*\\),\\([^,]*\\)$/\\3;\\2;\\1/\\<CR>\")\ncall setreg('c', \"gUUA;OK\\<Esc>\")\n:%normal! @a\n:%normal! @b\n:%normal! @c\n:wq\nEOF\n",
      "duration": 0.3
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "vim -Nu NONE -n -Es /app/input.csv -S /app/apply_macros.vim\n",
      "duration": 25.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cmp -s /app/input.csv /app/expected.csv && echo MATCH || (echo MISMATCH; diff -u /app/input.csv /app/expected.csv | head -n 50)\n",
      "duration": 1.0
    }
  ],
  "task_complete": false
}

